style.
  @page {
    margin-top: 0.5in;
    margin-left: 0;
    margin-right: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @page:first {
    margin-top: 0in;
  }

  body {
        user-select: none;
        -moz-user-select: none;
        -khtml-user-select: none;
        -webkit-user-select: none;
        -o-user-select: none;
  } 

div.style-flat
  img.header-art(src="/images/pages/admin/outcomes-report/arryn.png")

  div.header
    div
      img.print-logo(src="/images/pages/base/logo.png")
    div
      h4 Outcomes Report
      h5 Nov 5, 1955 - Jan 1, 2015

  div.address
    p 
      b Some place
      |, 301 Pine St, San Francisco, CA 94109
      br
      b Teacher: 
      if view.options.teacher.fullName
        | #{view.options.teacher.fullName} (#{view.options.teacher.email})
      else
        | #{view.options.teacher.email}
    p 
      b Account Manager: 
      | #{view.options.accountManager.fullName} (#{view.options.accountManager.email})

  div.block
    h1 Course Progress
    for course in view.courses
      div.course.dont-break
        h3= course.name
        div.bar
          div.el
            svg(width=100, height=100)
              circle.bottom(r=50,cx=50,cy=50)
              circle.top(r=25,cx=50,cy=50,style="stroke-dasharray: #{158/100*course.completion} 158")
              
          div.el
            div.big #{course.completion}%
            div.under complete
          div.el
            div.big 30
            div.under students
          div.el
            b Key Concepts:
            ul
              li Basic Syntax
              li Loops
              li Variables

  div.dont-break.block
    h1 Summary
    h4 Using CodeCombat's personalized learning engine, your students wrote
    div.fakebar
      div
        | 150 
        small computer programs
    h4 across an estimated...
    div.fakebar
      div
        | 123,3456 
        small lines of code
    h4 and expressed creativity by building
    div.fakebar
      div
        | 30 
        small standalone game and web projects



  div.dont-break.block
    div.rob-row
      div.left-col
        h2 Insights
        p.
          Tilde drinking vinegar plaid, yr dreamcatcher williamsburg flexitarian man braid godard umami disrupt cardigan before they sold out brooklyn poke. Cliche beard single-origin coffee celiac quinoa, prism ethical. Slow-carb pug skateboard chicharrones gochujang 3 wolf moon, 8-bit kickstarter cronut cliche edison bulb tilde kinfolk mlkshk wayfarers. Chartreuse gluten-free kombucha hashtag, polaroid meggings health goth small batch intelligentsia seitan distillery hot chicken coloring book 8-bit church-key. Synth chicharrones man bun gochujang biodiesel. Roof party poke typewriter whatever, letterpress salvia gastropub kombucha man bun. Fashion axe brooklyn deep v mixtape neutra.
      
      div.right-col
        h2 Classes
        for clazz in view.classes
          b= clazz.name
          ul
            li Language: python
            li 12 students

  div.dont-break
    img.anya(src="/images/pages/admin/outcomes-report/captain-pose.png")
    div.block.room-for-anya
      h1 Standards Coverage
      p.
        The full CodeCombat curriculum covers major programming standards in
        several widely-adopted frameworks, including those of the International
        Society for Technology in Education (ISTE), the Computer Science Teacher
        Association (CSTA), and the K-12 Computer Science Framework.

      p.
        At CodeCombat, we believe that students will be most prepared for both
        real-world computing jobs and further study of computer science by using
        real, typed code in full programming languages, so instead of using blockbased
        visual programming languages for beginners, we teach Python and
        JavaScript â€“the same languages used widely today by companies ranging
        from Google to the New York Times.

    div.bottom
      p Have question or want more information? We'd be happy to help.
      p
        | Reach out your Account Manager at 
        a(href="mailto:" + view.options.accountManager.email)= view.options.accountManager.email 
